Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a logic called MMSNP and presents a new proof of the reduction to finite-domain CSPs using universal-algebraic approach to study the computational complexity of MMSNP.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper mentions graph theory and finite model theory, which are closely related to data structures and algorithms.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another likely category as the paper deals with the computational complexity of MMSNP and presents a complexity dichotomy conjecture for CSPs in MMSNP.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with a logic that can be used to express queries in finite model theory, which is a subfield of AI.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a possible category as the paper deals with graph theory and finite model theory, which are subfields of discrete mathematics.
